name: 256-QAM Uplink
summary: The feature increases the maximum throughput and spectral efficiency by adding higher

parameters.name: INTERNAL_PER_UE_TRAFFIC_REP
parameters.description: The total number of occasions an uplink grant is meant for HARQ                                     transmission of a transport block. It uses 256-QAM modulation in                                     the uplink direction where DTX is the reason for no reception of                                     HARQ in uplink in the eNodeB. Only SCell traffic is                                     included.

parameters.name: INTERNAL_PER_UE_TRAFFIC_REP
parameters.description: The total number of occasions an uplink grant is meant for HARQ                                     transmission of a transport block. It uses 256-QAM                                     modulation in the uplink direction where DTX is the reason for                                     no reception of HARQ in uplink in the eNodeB. Only PCell traffic                                     is included.

parameters.name: INTERNAL_PER_UE_TRAFFIC_REP
parameters.description: The total number of unsuccessful HARQ transmissions in the uplink                                     direction using 256-QAM modulation. Failure is based on the CRC                                     check which resulted in a NACK. Only SCell traffic is                                     included.

parameters.name: INTERNAL_PER_UE_TRAFFIC_REP
parameters.description: The total number of successful HARQ transmissions in the uplink                                     direction using 256-QAM modulation. Successful transmissions are                                     based on the CRC check, not based on if RBS sends HARQ ACK. RBS                                     can use the ACK even if the transport block is not successfully                                     decoded in a way to control the HARQ. Only SCell traffic is                                     included.
